parameters: Clea (If we don't complete the request...)
Clea (If we don't complete the request...)

Clea: This is the Kasaro Bathhouse. It's really big, isn't
it?

Sophia the priestess: This is the bathhouse that was built
by the noble Kasaro. It seems it was made to gather votes to
become a member of the Senate.
Nora the thief: It's amazing! Water is coming out, water!

Mage Relm: Please don't get too excited, hehe. Unlike me,
you seem quite childish!
Stolge of Affection: Oh, you've finally arrived.
Clea: Sorry to keep you waiting. What should we do here?

Stolge of Affection: Well, to put it simply, it's like a big
cleaning. First, let's negotiate the price with the person
in charge here.

Stolge of Affection: Guild work isn't just about fighting,
you know.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Welcome, everyone from the
Adventurer's Guild! Please, have a seat.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Now, let me confirm the request
once again.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: I would like to request the
extermination of pests. We have never had such a problem
before, but they suddenly appeared.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: A large number of bugs have
appeared and our employees are at their wits' end.

Stolge of Affection: I see, so the work will be done at
night, right?

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Yes, could you please come during a
time when there are no customers?

Stolge of Affection: Just in case... If we were able to find
a fundamental solution, would it be possible to increase the
reward?
Bathhouse Manager Caron: Yes, of course...

Stolge of Affection: Alright, understood! Then, tonight,
I'll have them investigate the interior.
Clea: Understood, please take care of us.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Please let us know when you're
ready. Please be aware that you won't be able to leave the
building during the night.
Mage Relm: Um, well, I kind of... dislike bugs...
Cleric Sophia: Well, I don't really like them either.

Mage Relm: Exactly!! They're so gross, so if possible, I'd
like to avoid battles.

Clea: I'm actually quite fine with them. I used to catch
them in the forest often.
Thief Nora: T-This was... emergency rations...

Thief Nora: I-I can actually eat them! There aren't many
places where you can eat them, but, ahaha...

Cleric Sophia: After we're done, shall we have a meal
together?
Thief Nora: R-Really, is it okay!?

Clea: Let's turn this into a meal once it's resolved. First,
let's investigate the men's bath.
Clea: It seems like she's not here.

Thief Nora: Steam is coming out, is it hot water instead of
regular water?

Priestess Sophia: Yes, the bathhouse should be heated with
firewood.

Mage Relm: An environment where a large number of bugs are
appearing... Perhaps the firewood is suspicious.
Clea: Alright, let's go through the women's bathhouse.
Mage Relm: Ugh...the sound of bugs' wings...it's disgusting.
Thief Nora: There's definitely something ahead!

Priestess Sophia: Let's finish quickly. The taste of alcohol
after finishing work is exceptional, you know.
Mage Relm: You've been drinking all this time, haven't you?
Priestess Sophia: Hic... Oh, right, I remember now~!

Bathhouse Manager: Oh, you've returned! Has the
extermination of the pests been completed?

Clea: It's completed, but they weren't natural pests, they
were artificially created.

Bathhouse Manager: Let's discuss the details while having a
meal! I will prepare it right away, so please enjoy!

Stolge of Affection: I'm sorry, but I'll join in on the
feast as well.

Bathhouse Manager: Oh no, it's all thanks to the adventurers
from the Adventurer's Guild.

Clea: --So, there was a man who controls bugs, so we
restrained him.

Bathhouse Manager: Hmm, perhaps they were a skinny employee
who couldn't fit in well here.

Bathhouse Manager: They're not necessarily bad people. It
would be great if they could reflect on what happened this
time...
Clea: I leave the punishment up to all of you.

Bathhouse Manager: Understood, I will go and talk to them.
Please continue enjoying your meal here, everyone.

Priestess Sophia: Stolge-san, did you notice the mastermind?
Hehe, this wine is really delicious, isn't it~

Stolge of Affection: Well, that's how it is. Whether there
is resentment or not, we always investigate it beforehand.

Stolge of Affection: It's the same for anything, but
investigation is crucial. In my case, I believe that
investigation is everything when it comes to requests.
Clea: Do different people have different methods?

Stolge of Affection: The only common point is the three
principles of the guild. After that, the resolution methods
vary depending on the person.

Stolge of Affection: In the end, you yourself will have to
search for the method to resolve the request.

Stolge of Affection: By the way, have you guys seen the
pedestal in the men's bath?

Priestess Sophia: By the way, there was an unnatural
pedestal. In the women's bath, there was a statue standing
on it.

Stolge of Affection: Kasaro, who constructed this place,
intended to install a statue of sisters. However, it seems
that one of them was stolen by the phantom thief Perno, so
only one is displayed in the end.

Stolge of Affection: There might be a request to retrieve
it. If that happens, would you be willing to take it on?
Clea (The phantom thief I met at the campus...)

Stolge of Affection: Well, I'll head back first. You guys
enjoy your meal and consider it as a reward.
Thief Nora: Yes, I'm enjoying it! It's delicious!!
Stolge of Affection: Hahaha, that was good.

Stolge of Affection: That's right, the manager wants you to
try out the baths and massages.
Clea: Understood, I'll drop by when I have some free time.
Thief Nora: Phew~ I'm so full! I'm completely satisfied!
Priestess Sophia: I thoroughly enjoyed it as well.

Mage Relm: Hehe, that was quite a meal! It was a hospitality
befitting a genius like me.
Clea: Your way of eating is messy, isn't it?
Mage Relm: W-What is it!? Are you picking on this genius!?
Clea: No, it's not like that.

Mage Relm: Hmph, my mood is ruined! Let's hurry back to our
adventure!!
Clea: Did I make her angry?

Priestess Sophia: Clea-chan grew up in a good environment,
so her way of eating is influenced by her upbringing and
surroundings.

Priestess Sophia: Maybe Relm-chan didn't have anyone to
teach her how to eat properly or to give her advice.
Clea: I was thoughtless... Let's go too.

Stolge of Affection: Some pests even have poison, so make
sure to prepare properly before dealing with them, okay?

Stolge of Affection: There must be something that is
creating these pests.

Stolge of Affection: I have a feeling something is going on
around here... Please be careful.
Bathhouse Manager Caro: Are you ready?

Bathhouse Manager Caro: Please let me know when you're
ready.

Bathhouse Manager Caro: Understood. Please wait here until
evening.

Bathhouse Manager Caro: Please come back here once
everything is resolved.

Bathhouse Manager: Thanks to everyone, the bathhouse has
become safe!

Bathhouse Manager Caro: Sarigari has returned, I can't
believe it, but at the same time, the statue of the sisters
has also returned!

Bathhouse Manager Caro: Sarigari is rumored to bring good
luck and has built a good relationship with the employees,
so I feel relieved.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Well, well, everyone! What can I do
for you today?

Sophia the Priestess: I've come in place of the firewood
craftsman, Torch-san.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: It's fortunate that he only has a
minor injury. There aren't many firewood craftsmen like him,
you know.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Here is your reward for
substituting for Torch-san, thank you very much.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Since the sisters have gathered,
it's been quite lively and busy.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: I apologize for the inconvenience,
but we have cleaning scheduled after this, even though you
came all this way.

Priestess Sophia: Please don't worry... By the way, can we
see the statue of the sisters in the men's bath?

Bathhouse Manager Caron: There was a time when mixed bathing
was allowed, but the discipline was disrupted, even by the
wishes of everyone.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: I apologize, but it is not allowed
for individuals of the opposite sex to enter from Casauro-
sama's side.

Priestess Sophia: Please don't worry... I was just curious
about the beautiful statue of the goddess.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: ...I have a favor to ask. Could you
please carry this firewood to the boiler room?

Bathhouse Manager Caron: By chance, there may be times when
you can see the men's bath.

Bathhouse Manager Caron: Please let me know when you're
ready.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Casaro Bathhouse Manager: We are currently cleaning, so
please follow a special route to the boiler room. Is that
okay with you?

Casaro Bathhouse Manager: There might be beasts, so it's
better to prepare before heading there.

Casaro Bathhouse Manager: This is a place that was used
during construction, so please be careful as you make your
way to the boiler room.

Bathhouse Manager: Thanks to everyone, the bathhouse has
become safe!

Explorer Armada: It's been a while since I've been to the
Kasaro Bathhouse. I used to come here often when I was
wandering around searching for literature.

Priestess Sophia: There's nothing quite like a drink after a
bath... Armada-san, of course you'll join us, right?

Explorer Armada: Haha, you've got quite the courage to
challenge the bottomless barrel that is Armada.
Thief Nora: I'm going to get scolded by Eleo-san again~!

Explorer Armada: Hey little one, you shouldn't give up on
growing just yet, okay?

Explorer Armada: Eat well, sleep well! Ahaha, that's how I
became so big.
Mage Relm: N-No, that's not it!

Mage Relm: What I want to say is, it's about that, the story
over there!

Clea: Are you talking about the scar on your back? I have a
feeling that it has become lighter compared to before.
Clea: Since I defeated the dragon, that might be the cause.

Priestess Phoni: It is said that the body and mind are
interconnected. I believe something has changed within you,
Clea-san.
Priestess Phoni: Hehe, I think that change is really good.

Explorer Armada: I had a feeling about it, but... hmm.

each person.

Thief Nora: Look! It seems like today's bath has the scent
of lilies!
Mage Relm: Sigh... Let's quickly get into the bathtub.

Clea: Could you please tell us your intentions soon?

Celis, the Swift Wind: You're just putting up with my
selfishness.
Celis, the Swift Wind: Let's take a bath together.

Celis, the Swift Wind: The scar on your back has faded,
hasn't it?

Clea: It has been three years since then, but I don't think
this scar will ever disappear.

Celis, the Swift Wind: Now, let's go in... Let's wash each
other's backs.

Clea: Every time the scar on my back fades, the old lady I
lived with was happy.

Clea: But I was scared. I felt like my resentment and hatred
towards the dragon were fading away.

Clea: I don't have any dreams. I only have goals to fulfill,
nothing else.

Clea: Anyone who stands in my way is an enemy, even if they
were once a comrade or someone important...
Celis, the Swift Wind: I'll pour the hot water.
Clea: Yes, thank you very much.
Celis, the Swift Wind: Now, let's get into the bathtub.

Clea: It feels nice... like the fatigue from our journey is
fading away.

Celis, the Swift Wind: Sometimes I come here alone. It's a
place where I can relax and it's suitable for deep thoughts.
Clea: Thank you very much, Celis-san.
Clea: Thank you for inviting me and being considerate.
Celis, the Swift Wind: Are you scared of crying, Clea?
Clea: Huh, what do you mean?

Celis, the Swift Wind: I wonder if you're scared that if you
cry once, everything will come pouring out.
Celis, the Swift Wind: It's okay, Clea.

Celis, the Swift Wind: You're not that weak. Even if you cry
or break down in tears, you will definitely be able to walk
forward from there.

Celis, the Swift Wind: That's why, it's okay to cry, you
know?

Clea: I... I... I... Ugh, I promised myself that I wouldn't
cry... Ugh...

Clea: On that day, my tears dried up...! The day my father
and mother were killed... But, ugh...

Clea: I-I'm not crying! This is just hot water, it's not my
tears!

Celis, the Swift Wind: Yeah, you're not crying. Let's take a
little more time here to relax.

Celis, the Swift Wind (I hope that someday she will be able
to cry in front of others)

Celis, the Swift Wind (Only those who can show their
weakness can truly become strong...)

Celis, the Swift Wind: Thank you for putting up with my
selfishness today.
Clea: Thank you very much as well.

Celis, the Swift Wind: If we defeat the dragon, will you
come with us again?
Clea: Yes. Please invite me normally next time.

Celis, the Swift Wind: A-And, I don't have many friends...
so I don't really know how to invite people...

Celis, the Swift Wind: Let's both survive the next request
and meet again at the Adventurer's Guild, Clea.
Celis, the Swift Wind: Well then, let's go.
